The Federal Government has reiterated its commitment to providing the needed humanitarian assistance to the vulnerable across the country as part of its commitment to coherently coordinate humanitarian assistance.  The Minister of Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development, Sadiya Umar Farouq who made this known at the opening of a maiden 2021 United Nations organized retreat in Abuja Friday said the two-day Humanitarian Country Team Retreat is positioned at seeking a lasting solutions to the crises in the North East.  She noted that Government is scaling up efforts to provide durable solutions for the return, reintegration and resettlement of affected communities adding that collaboration is needed from all relevant stakeholders, continuous interaction and cooperation between the Humanitarian Country Team, the Federal Government, Security Agencies and other relevant actors.